                            <comment id="15093735" author="srowen" created="Tue, 12 Jan 2016 11:01:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the example needs an update, but not for this reason. There&apos;s no separate &quot;memory space&quot; in local mode. It&apos;s one JVM. However it&apos;s undefined whether the copy of &lt;tt&gt;counter&lt;/tt&gt; is the same or different in this case. Actually, I find a copy is serialized with the closure at this point so the result is still 0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the explanation should be changed to say the result is undefined here, and could be 0 or not, and explain why. Do you want to try a PR?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15096661" author="mortada" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 17:45:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, sure definitely. I&apos;ll create a PR and link to this JIRA ticket. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
